                <para id="import-auto-id1325772">The 1965 Voting Rights Act was preceded by Lyndon Johnson’s signing of the 1964 Civil Rights Act. Both articles were instrumental in establishing equal rights for African Americans. Check out Cornell University’s website on this topic to learn more about this civil rights legislation: <link url="http://openstax.org/l/Cornell_civil_rights">http://openstax.org/l/Cornell_civil_rights</link></para></section>
